Dear Shri Shiva Dasa ji,

Shaantho Bhava

 

1.       Its so nice of you to have taken time to respond to my request.

2.       The idea of "janeyu' or "yagnyopavita" is very excellent, and even
I did not think of it, and I am very delighted to know this refreshing idea.
Had my child been a boy, this would have been surely worked out. But she is
a girl. Can you think for something similar to yagnyopaveeta or janeyu for
girls please? Because this is a really nice idea.

3.       My dear Shiva Dasa Ji, on one hand you say that the entire creation
is made by Shakti; so all mud, pedestal etc is Shakti, and on the other hand
you say "to abandon reliance on material objects" which means to avoid
Shakti. I think all material or matter is Shakti-swaroopa, am I right? I am
getting confused by the apparent contradiction in your idea, and unable to
understand your point. Please forgive me and help me to understand it better
please.

4.       Dear Shiva Dasa Ji, if you are speaking then it means you have
respect for the listeners/readers. You cannot speak of something which you
are unsure of, and expect your listeners to carry a packet of salt to eat
every time they read/listen to you. This is a kind of insult to the
readers/listeners. When you are speaking, make sure that you have made
enough sincere efforts to be truthful and authentic, so that people who
read/listen to you do not need to take salt. By the way, I don't like to eat
salts J.(just a light mood please)

 

Thank you so much.

 

Warm Regards,

Kannan

 

