Pranaam :)

 

One can use it like a "Janivara" that brahmins wear which goes over one of
the shoulders crossing across the torso. Fairly invisible under a shirt.

 

In an unrelated note: One can also take this as an indication to abandon
reliance on material objects and let the Rudraksh get established in mind
(or Chitta) which no one can object. However since entire creation was made
by Mother Shakti to entertain my beloved Lord Shiva; feet or head, mud or
pedestal, everything there is - it is holy :). Like the saying goes "kan kan
me Raam"

 

Jai Shri Raam :)

 

I totally do not qualify to comment on ritual matters and humbly request you
to take my words with handful of salt :)




